                            <comment id="130822" author="pjones" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2015 21:41:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok Jay&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="130820" author="jaylan" created="Mon, 19 Oct 2015 21:13:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please close it as WONT FIX.&lt;br/&gt;
We are not going to use 2.6 and not sure if next lustre would be 2.7 or 2.8 and we most likely would be running sles12 at that time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will open a new case if we still hit this problem on next generation of lustre and kernel.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98512" author="pjones" created="Thu, 6 Nov 2014 11:55:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jay&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is not presently a plan to do this but if this is something that NASA would like to run in production this is certainly something that we could help with.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="98483" author="jaylan" created="Wed, 5 Nov 2014 22:51:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is there plan to port &quot;kernel update for 3.0.101-0.35&quot; and &quot;kernel update for 3.0.101-0.40&quot; to b2_6?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are running 3.0.101-0.31. Our next kernel would be 3.0.101-0.40.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="97682" author="bogl" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2014 13:48:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is fixed in master.  The kernel update mod for 3.0.101-0.35, commit 3000a83dcd3c201f383c0507d33e7861fc695997, includes changes to take care of this. To quote from the commit header:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Create and use ll_d_count() wrapper to solve&lt;br/&gt;
build problem caused by linux #include changes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b2_6 doesn&apos;t have this mod &amp;amp; therefore can not build on the latest sles11sp3 kernels.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="97655" author="pjones" created="Tue, 28 Oct 2014 01:55:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please comment on this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
